rkets always are) by unscrupulous people like Yantis.  Surely they foresaw that there would be a market for plat.  Even grade-schoolers have heard of "supply and demand."  <i>Again,</i> it's how the world works.  We don't stop being human beings just because we're playing a game.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="1" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br />I feel sorry for the dumb mofos that buy this crap.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></font id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"><br /><br />I feel sorry for the dumb mofos that buy all sorts of tangible goods, but it's their money to spend.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="1" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br />I  can almost agree that selling an account should be ok, because you shelled out $$ for all the disks etc..  Better someone enjoys your account then have 3-4 yrs go down the tubes.  Selling pp/items is a bit different, because they pharm/exploit EQ and introduce way more pp/items then would normally be seen.<br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></font id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"><br /><br />Unfortunately, inflation over time is inevitable in a game like this.  Every time a mob dies, new money is "created" out of thin air.  Further, there's nothing wrong with farming in and of itself.  To some people, amassing wealth is the only goal left to attain in this game, for some it's the only "kick" they still get out of it, even if they're <i>not</i> selling the proceeds.<br /><br />The blame here lies squarely with SOE, for 3 reasons:<br /><br />1. Given that inflation is naturally inevitable in a game where money is constantly coming into existance, they should have put in counter-measures (plat sinks) LONG AGO, like the casino, something I've rallied for for years.  Not only did they NOT do this when they should have, once they finally got around to doing it, they fucking took it down after a day or two.  A casino is the perfect plat-sink, and it should be permanent.  <br /><br />2. But letting the natural inflation go unchecked wasn't good enough for these morons.  They had to let these plat-duping bugs remain in-game for months upon months, bringing more plat into the game than probably would have shown up for God knows how long.  They ridiculously cared more about XP exploits.  Wonder how much faster that lvl 10 with 2million plat to blow on equipment is going to level even without exploits or power-leveling?  Fucking gimp retards.  <br /><br />3.  Like drugs in the real world, or alcohol during prohibition, they <i>created</i> the black market that made Yanti what he is.  This is inevitable when you "outlaw" something that you know damn good and well people are going to buy anyway.  They could have prevented this problem <i>and</i> made themselves buttloads of "tax" money in the process.<br /><br />Inexcusable idiocy (and perhaps even complicity in the case of some people) on the part of Sony is the cause of all these woes, in my very sincere opinion.<br /><br /><br /><br />  <br /><br /></span></font></td>
